{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Mandatory warnings for venues and businesses that use strobe/flashing lights",
        "additional_details": "There are many conditions that mean people can have an adverse reaction to strobe or flashing lights - such as photosensitive seizures, autism, ADHD, sensory processing disorder, migraines and many more. \r\n \r\nWhen going out, some places have strobe/flashing lighting with no warning (bars, restaurants, clubs, etc), this can make going out and trying to live our lives very difficult.\r\n",
        "background": "It should be mandatory to display warnings at entrances of venues or businesses that have strobe/flashing lighting. Businesses should also be required put information about the use of lighting at any addresses they are responsible for on their websites.",
